DynamicTemplateString.SourceText: While Material.io generally uses Scale-Independent Pixels (sp) to specify font size units and type scale, the operating unit in FileMaker is the pixel independent unit, pt. To adapt Material.io font and typography guidelines to FileMaker, we have cast Material font sizes and type scales in FileMaker friendly terms borrowing scaling specifications and a few labels from Apple's Design Guidelines.

DynamicTemplateString.SourceText: Mizu is a grid based theme. Objects measurements align to an 64pt, 8 minor step FileMaker grid, which in turn, informs both spacing between components and of the overall layout.Smaller components, such as icons and typography, can align to a 4pt grid.A basic 1280pt wide layout grid template can be found on this layout or in the 'Grids' folder in this file. This template has been specifically designed to create evenly spaced 16pt gutters that work for 1280 and 1024 wide layouts.
